title: Alan Moore: Top Ten (America's Best Comics)
description:
IMO one of the best things Alan Moore created, along with Tom Strong, both series never gained that much attention despite the name attached to them

The detail level in the artwork is really Geof-Darrow-esque insane

Top 10 is a limited series created and written by Alan Moore and illustrated by Gene Ha and Zander Cannon. The series lasted for 12 issues from 1999 to 2001 and led to several spin-off; see below. The story is about the day-to-day lives and work of the police officers of Neopolis, a city that is home to all the super-powered beings -- everyone has super powers and is wearing colorful costumes in Neopolis -- and that is protected by the 10th Police Precinct and the Top 10 team.
